<br>
If I run into Blackburrow and kill EVERYTHING in the zone, regardless of whether or not it's camped, who am I affecting? It's my game, it's my right to kill those spawns, as long as they aren't fighting someone else (by Verant rules). <br>
<br>
If a server population of 2000-3000 people or more (the planes capable people) on the server agree to a rotation system that gives them equal shots at the mobs in the planes, and 20 people start taking those spawns, killing them everytime they pop and keeping others from getting to them, who is that affecting? <br>
<br>
You see, if Shattering Steel were actually doing this to HELP the server, i.e. trying to figure out a better system that is even more fair for all, I'd be right there with them. I'd be working with them to do what I can. But they aren't. They've made no attempts to work with the server population. They've been asked politely to work with the rest of the KGC to help the server, and they have rebuffed us, with sarcasm and spite. They have twice messed up respawn times on non-American guilds, and all they have managed is to farm some armour out of the planes, for themselves. They haven't offered to create a better system, they have only said &quot;I'll get what I think is mine and no one can tell me I can't have it.&quot; I have PERSONALLY urged them to seek peace and respect the community on the server, which they laughed at. <br>
<br>
Now I don't condone verbal harrassment per se. But shunning them, you betcha. It's the only method of enforcement we have. I ask that anyone who does follow the ban do so politely and always explain why. Because I do not think all members of SS are bad. I think they are misled, and their guild leader is leading them in selfish attempts to be vindicitive to people on the server who he has it out for. To those members of SS who don't understand the uproar, I'll personally explain it to you, with history about the server and previous attempts to go FFA. <br>
<br>
One last thing... if you've never run a raid that involves and needs more than 2 groups, I urge you to do so. Run that raid, see how much work goes into it, and then stop and think about what would happen if you set a raid to go to the Hole for instance. You plan for a week, you spend hours going over attendance and making groups and moving the groups and keeping 40 people together. And you set up the raid with the understanding that you would be alone in doing it, because the other guilds who could have done it agreed to let you have it that day with no interference as long as you didn't interfere with their raid the next day. And you spend 4 hours getting to your goal, with ports and attendance, etc. and finally you get there.. and it's empty. Because someone who KNOWS about your schedule and KNOWS that you are coming there gets there first and takes it all, and then guess what? You have to wait 12-14 hours for the stuff to respawn. Feel good? Is that helping the server? <br>
<br>
That's what these guys are doing. They are parasites, ticks on the testicles of this server. <br>
<br>
